141    /**
142    * The main component class of the RapidMiner GUI. The class holds a lot of Actions that can be used
143    * for the tool bar and for the menu bar. MainFrame has methods for handling the process (saving,
144    * opening, creating new). It keeps track of the state of the process and enables/disables buttons.
145    * It must be notified whenever the process changes and propagates this event to its children. Most
146    * of the code is enclosed within the Actions.
147    *
148    * @author Ingo Mierswa, Simon Fischer, Sebastian Land, Marius Helf, Jan Czogalla
149    */
150    @SuppressWarnings("deprecation")
 
0% Uncovered Elements: 2 (2) Complexity: 1 Complexity Density: 1

153    /**

1648    /**
1649    * Checks the current process for potential problems. If a problem is deemed big enough (e.g. an
1650    * operator that requires input but is not connected), returns {@code true}. If no showstoppers
1651    * are found, returns {@code false}. This method also alerts the user about the problems so
1652    * after it returns, nothing else needs to be done.
1653    *
1654    * @return {@code true} if the process contains a problem which should prevent process
1655    * execution; {@code false} otherwise
1656    */
 
- Uncovered Elements: 0 (0) Complexity: 1 Complexity Density: -
1657    private boolean doesProcessContainShowstoppers() {...
1658    // prevent two bubbles on top of each other
1659    getProcessPanel().getOperatorWarningHandler().killWarningBubble();
1660   
1661    // if any operator has a mandatory parameter with no value and no default value. As it
1662    // cannot predict execution behavior (e.g. Branch operators), this may turn up problems
1663    // which would not occur during process execution
1664    Process process = getProcess();
1665    Pair<Operator, ParameterType> missingParamPair = ProcessTools.getOperatorWithoutMandatoryParameter(process);
1666    if (missingParamPair != null) {
1667    // if there is already one of these, kill
1668    if (missingParameterBubble != null) {
1669    missingParameterBubble.killBubble(true);
1670    }
1671   
1672    missingParameterBubble = ProcessGUITools.displayPrecheckMissingMandatoryParameterWarning(
1673    missingParamPair.getFirst(), missingParamPair.getSecond());
1674    return true;
1675    }
1676   
1677    // if any port needs data but is not connected. As it cannot predict execution behavior
1678    // (e.g. Branch operators), this may turn up problems which would not occur during
1679    // process execution
1680    Port missingInputPort = ProcessTools.getPortWithoutMandatoryConnection(process);
1681    if (missingInputPort != null) {
1682    // if there is already one of these, kill
1683    if (missingInputBubble != null) {
1684    missingInputBubble.killBubble(true);
1685    }
1686   
1687    missingInputBubble = ProcessGUITools.displayPrecheckInputPortDisconnectedWarning(missingInputPort);
1688    return true;
1689    }
1690   
1691    // if there is already one of these, kill
1692    if (noResultConnectionBubble != null) {
1693    noResultConnectionBubble.killBubble(true);
1694    }
1695   
1696    // if the process has no connected result ports and the last executed
1697    // process root child operator does not prevent a warning bubble we need
1698    // to notify the user that no output port is connected
1699    boolean isWarnOnNoResultProcess = Boolean
1700    .parseBoolean(ParameterService.getParameterValue(RapidMinerGUI.PROPERTY_SHOW_NO_RESULT_WARNING));
1701    if (isWarnOnNoResultProcess) {
1702    boolean connectedResultPort = ProcessTools.isProcessConnectedToResultPort(process);
1703    Operator lastExecutedProcessRootChild = ProcessTools.getLastExecutedRootChild(process);
1704    if (!connectedResultPort && lastExecutedProcessRootChild != null
1705    && !ResultWarningPreventionRegistry.isResultWarningSuppressed(lastExecutedProcessRootChild)) {
1706    noResultConnectionBubble = ProcessGUITools.displayPrecheckNoResultPortInformation(process);
1707    return true;
1708    }
1709    }
1710   
1711    // no showstopper
1712    return false;
